<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Description==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''Std AlignToSelection''' command points the camera in the active [[3D_View|3D View]] in the direction of the normal of a face, the normal of a plane defined by a planar curved edge, or the direction of a straight edge. {{Version|26.3}}: If multiple elements are selected that define multiple normals, the average of the normals is used.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The final direction of the camera is the direction of the normal, or its opposite, whichever is closest to the previous camera direction.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Usage==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select one ({{VersionMinus|1.1}}) or more ({{VersionPlus|26.3}}) faces or edges the 3D View.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Std_AlignToSelection.svg|16px]] [[Std_AlignToSelection|Align to Selection]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|View → Standard Views → [[Image:Std_AlignToSelection.svg|16px]] Align to Selection}} option from the menu.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Std_AlignToSelection.svg|16px]] Align to Selection}} option from the [[3D_View|3D View]] context menu.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Std_AlignToSelection.svg|16px]] Align to Selection}} option from the Mini-cube menu of the [[Navigation_Cube|Navigation Cube]].
</div>


